    "recap_headline": "Florida Atlantic University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BOCA RATON, Fla. \u00a0\u2013\nFlorida Atlantic baseball downed Presbyterian 7-2 on Wednesday afternoon to complete a two-game midweek sweep. The Owls have won five straight heading into this weekend's series with UMBC.\nTHE BEGINNING\nPresbyterian (2-16) scored in the first inning before the Owls (11-6) responded with two runs in the second. A walk and an infield single preceded a throwing error by the PC first baseman. Florida Atlantic added the second run on a groundout double play.\nTHE TURNING POINT\nThe Owls began to pull away with two runs in the fourth inning and one in the fifth. An RBI double to left center off the bat of\nTJ Gramesty\nin the fourth drove in\nEli Small\nfrom second base.\nMarshall Lipsey\nfollowed with a single up the middle to cash in Gramesty. In the fifth,\nXavier Moronta\nsent an opposite-field, two-out double to the left field corner and scored when\nPatrick Ward\npoked a single through the right side to make it 5-1.\nTHE FINISH\nLipsey launched his second home run of the season with one out in the sixth. The two-run blast into the bullpen in right field put the Owls up 7-1. PC scored a consolation run in the eighth, but the home side held on to complete the two-game sweep.\nQUOTABLE\nHead Coach\nJohn McCormack\nPostgame with\n@FAUCoachMac\n#WIP\n\ud83c\udfdd\ufe0f\npic.twitter.com/0HfK0hpqZU\n\u2014 Florida Atlantic Baseball (@FAUBaseball)\nMarch 11, 2026\nTHE BATS\nWith two run-scoring hits, including the home run, Lipsey upped his RBI total to 11 for the season.\nMoronta reached base four times by way of a double, a single, and two walks.\nGramesty recorded his third multi-hit game of the season.\nTHE ARMS\nFreshman\nBrody Juntunen\nmade his first career start and allowed one run in two innings.\nReilly Witmer\nand\nCarson Kimball\ncombined to hold the Blue Hose scoreless from the third through fifth innings.\nBryan Boully\nhandled the sixth and seventh frames. The fifth-year senior struck out three.\nZach Kilby\nallowed a run in the eighth before handing it off to\nKyzer Smith\nfor a clean ninth to close it out.\nTHE DEFENSE\nThe Owls turned two double plays, neither of which was conventional.\nIn the second inning, Lipsey fired a seed from centerfield to third base to cut down a runner trying to tag up from second.\nIn the fifth inning, after another double, Ward snared a line drive down the first base line and doubled up the runner at second\nWHAT'S NEXT\nThe Owls will look to extend their winning streak to six on Friday night when UMBC comes to town to start a three-game series. First pitch is set for 6:35 p.m.\nFOLLOW THE OWLS\nTo stay up to date on all things Florida Atlantic baseball, follow us on social media @faubaseball."
